# Backend endpoints the client talks to. Copy to .env for local builds; .env is
# gitignored so real endpoints never land in the repo.
#
# Local dev — plaintext is fine (dev bundles aren't distributed):
VITE_FILM_BASE=https://film.example.com
VITE_AUTH_BASE=https://auth.example.com
#
# Release builds (CI) do NOT use the plaintext vars. Instead they inject an
# obfuscated form — VITE_FILM_BASE_ENC / VITE_AUTH_BASE_ENC = base64 of the
# reversed URL — derived in the workflow from the repository secrets
# (VITE_FILM_BASE / VITE_AUTH_BASE), so the real domains never appear as
# plaintext in the shipped APK/.wgt. config.js decodes them at runtime.
